1. I have the machine learning (ML) in the third year, plus 4 seminar groups:
- I would like the course to precede my seminars ;
- I would like very much to not take hours Mondays and Tuesdays (when preparing the course of that week;
- I can not keep hours in the morning from 8 to 10 (morning revives me hard ... I got older);
- I'd rather have the afternoon and evening hours;
- Obviously I prefer that the hours be grouped if possible four in a row (courses to the 2 Half-year to be one after another (or at least in the same day), and seminars will be grouped 2 in a row, so I will have "to work 4 hours in a row when coming to FII).
2. In regards to my collaborators, ie people who will hold seminars on this subject:
Stefan A. Pantiru (computer, external collaborator)
- Has 4 seminar groups and wants to have classes grouped (2 each seminar, so 4 hours) or morning between 8-12, or in the evening between the hours of 16 to 20;
- NOT hold classes on Wednesdays.
B. Tiberius Dumitru (assistant, PhD., UT "Gh.")
- Has 2 seminar groups; He wants to keep his classes Friday evening (16-20); has a very busy schedule at UT "Gh.," very much so please try to keep in mind his option.
C. There are 5 more seminar groups; it will be all hold by freelancers, so you should put all them in the morning (4 hours) or evening (4 hours). Later today or tomorrow I will indicate the names of these employees (I am negotiating with them, but I did not take the final decision yet).
3. The problem of a "special seminar" on the machine learning to come to the best students in the third year.
I guess the lack of resources (time available halls and timetable) such a seminar can not be put in zone sometime else than Saturday or another day but only in the evening after 20 o'clock ,so I should discuss with students at the course in the first week and decide. For now you can pass it on Saturday mornings (but not at 8).
IMPORTANT:
I prefer courses room 309 and possibly 112.
Also prefer special seminar room 309.
In general, for my seminars I prefer rooms with two tables, but they are few, far as I know ... I do not know how occupied is the room 2010, but I'd probably like to hold seminars there.
I (LC): 3 groups + "special seminar"
Restrictions: Do not months, Tuesday, and in the other day from 8 am NOT.
Preferences: my seminars to be made after the course (in the same week)
"Special Seminar" can be placed between the hours 20-21: 40 (Wednesday-Friday) or Saturday from 10am. I urge C309. (Of course, if you can put sometime Wednesday-Friday between 10 to 20 I will not refuse.)
*Liviu Ciortuz*

Catalin Barjoveanu
In semester 1 , I have: 1 course at MSI2 Security Software + MISS2 (preferably seminar room C901 or C909 with laptop + video because there is better seen in video) 1 Security Software Laboratory in MSI2 (room laboratory laptop + video) 1 Security Software Laboratory in MISS2 (room laboratory laptop + video) 2 laboratories of Information Security at Year 3 (laboratory room) -------------------------------------------------- -------------------
That restriction, masks COURSE I want to be preferable from Tuesday 8-10; if you can not Tuesday at 8, then Tuesday 10-12 or 16-18.
2 LABORATORIES masks: if the course is set in the morning (8-10 or 10-12), laboratories I want to be grouped in one day on 16-20. If the course is set at 16, I'd like a laboratory after class and one in a 8 morning.
2 LABORATORIES information security from 3rd year I want to be made grouped as possible with the other hours.
I do not want hours after 16:00 but only once a week.
